bilingual.source: You can add chicken to your salad.
bilingual.target: 你可以在色拉中加入鸡肉。

bilingual.source: The dressing on this salad is delicious.
bilingual.target: 这道色拉的调料很好吃。

bilingual.source: The salad at this restaurant is very fresh.
bilingual.target: 这家餐厅的色拉非常新鲜。

bilingual.source: We need to buy some vegetables to make a salad.
bilingual.target: 我们需要买一些蔬菜来做色拉。

bilingual.source: To make the salad, you should add some salad oil.

bilingual.source: Oh , and French dressing on the salad, please.

list.abstract: Salad，英 [ˈsæləd]，美 [ˈsæləd]，英语单词。名词为色拉，沙拉，凉拌菜，生菜。短语搭配：fruit salad水果色拉；一排勋章。 例句为：”At the age of six, I could make vegetable salad.六岁时，我会做蔬菜沙拉。”

yingyinNormal.en: The footprints are being made by ants. They're collecting leaves to eat. Are they going to have salad for lunch? Yes. Talking of lunch, let's have our picnic.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些是蚂蚁弄出来的小脚印。他们在收拾树叶来吃。他们会吃色拉当午餐吗？会的。说到午餐，我们来野餐吧。

yingyinNormal.en: There's pineapple shrimp and lemon shrimp, coconut shrimp, pepper shrimp, shrimp soup, shrimp stew, shrimp salad, shrimp in potatoes, shrimp burger, shrimp sandwich. That's about it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有菠萝虾、柠檬虾、椰子虾、胡椒虾、鲜虾汤、油焖虾、虾肉色拉、土豆虾、虾肉汉堡包、虾肉三明治。还有…差不多就这些了。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't you like the salad? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 难道你不喜欢沙拉吗？不喜欢。

yingyinNormal.en: I want you to make me a delicious salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想让你帮我做些美味的沙拉。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, dear, George. Don't you like the salad? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，亲爱的，乔治，难道你不喜欢沙拉吗？不喜欢。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, dear, George. Don't you like the salad? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，亲爱的，乔治，难道你不喜欢沙拉吗？不喜欢。

yingyinNormal.en: I've ordered chicken and salad and cake for 150.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我订了一百五十人份的鸡肉，沙拉和蛋糕。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm going to make you my chunky bacon and cucumber salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要做的是培根黄瓜沙拉。

yingyinNormal.en: What's going on? I made her favorite, tuna salad with pickles.
yingyinNormal.zh: 发生了什么事？我帮她带了腌黄瓜鱿鱼三明治。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't worry. We're planning to have sex right on the salad bar.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别担心，我们正打算在沙拉吧上云雨一番咧。

yingyinNormal.en: Granny Pig has made the tomatoes, lettuce and cucumber into a salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪奶奶已经把西红柿，生菜和黄瓜做成了蔬菜。

yingyinNormal.en: Granny Pig has made the tomatoes, lettuce and cucumber into a salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪奶奶已经把西红柿，生菜和黄瓜做成了蔬菜。

yingyinNormal.en: Granny Pig has made the tomatoes, lettuce and cucumber into a salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪奶奶已经把西红柿，生菜和黄瓜做成了蔬菜。

yingyinNormal.en: Pickle? Pickles make her sick. Giving her pickles is like giving me salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 腌黄瓜？那会让她想吐，让她吃腌黄瓜就像让我吃沙拉。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, on trees, but then they fall, and they rot, like salad in the fridge.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，树上的叶子是绿的，但它们凋落后，就会腐烂就像冰箱里的沙拉一样。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe George will like the vegetables when they're made into a lovely salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许乔治会喜欢蔬菜。当他们被做成一道可口的沙拉的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe George will like the vegetables when they're made into a lovely salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许乔治会喜欢蔬菜。当他们被做成一道可口的沙拉的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe George will like the vegetables when they're made into a lovely salad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许乔治会喜欢蔬菜。当他们被做成一道可口的沙拉的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: There's salad. There's food, you wait there until I get back. You'll be safe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有吃的，你在这儿等着我回来，你会安全的。

yingyinNormal.en: No! Rachel just had that salad, and Joey with his like teeny pizza! It's just...
yingyinNormal.zh: 不行，瑞秋只点了那盘小沙拉，乔伊只吃了那片小披萨。
